eNCA’s Siphamandla Goge has the details. #eNCA #DStv403  JOHANNESBURG - One of the most important events on the AmaZulu calendar is on track for 28 May. King MisuZulu KaZwelithini wants to keep most of his coronation local. He says the traditional parts of the ceremony will be held in KwaNongoma. The monarch addressed a meeting of the royal family following his official recognition by President Cyril Ramaphosa. eNCA’s Siphamandla Goge has the details in the video above.